## Polish Cycle 5 -- Epic Plan

Since **all 5 review cycles failed** (every reviewer crashed/timed out), I performed a thorough manual audit of the entire codebase. The product is well-architected with strong test coverage, strict TypeScript, and solid audio engineering. The polish work targets the gap between "it works" and "it's exceptional."

### 5 Epics Created

| # | Epic ID | Title | Priority | Focus |
|---|---------|-------|----------|-------|
| 1 | `long-running-harness-7sa` | QA verification via browser automation | P1 | Runtime verification -- no browser testing has occurred |
| 2 | `long-running-harness-fyp` | Error resilience and recovery hardening | P2 | Stuck states, unhandled rejections, missing timeouts |
| 3 | `long-running-harness-cya` | Design system token compliance | P2 | Hardcoded hex/px values violating token system |
| 4 | `long-running-harness-k0e` | Accessibility hardening and focus management | P2 | Focus return, keyboard alternatives, aria labels |
| 5 | `long-running-harness-imy` | Interaction craft and delightful details | P2 | Bezier cables, micro-animations, branded startup |

### Dependencies
```
QA Verification (7sa) ─┬─> Error Resilience (fyp)
                       ├─> Token Compliance (cya)
                       ├─> Accessibility (k0e)
                       └─> Interaction Craft (imy)
```

QA runs first (P1) to catch any runtime issues. The 4 fix epics run in parallel after QA completes.

